text: Gloucestershire County Cricket Club was founded (created) in 1870. The team has first-class status, and plays in the County Championship. The team plays its home games in both Bristol and Cheltenham. Gloucestershire's famous players have included W. G. Grace, Walter Hammond, Mike Procter, and Courtney Walsh.
